es of the discontinued friaries. For the first time these orders are treated comparatively: the volume offers a total history, from their origins, spirituality and pastoral impact, to their music, buildings and runaways.FRANCES ANDREWS teaches at the University of St Andrews and is the author of The Early Humiliati (CUP 1999).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMonasticism and religious ordersxEuropexHistory, Middle Ages, 600-1500. 0aMonasticism and religious orderszEuropexHistoryyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 4aHistory of Religion. 4aMedieval History. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh  aAugustinians.  aCarmelites.  aMedieval monastic orders.  aPied Friars.  aSack Friars.1 aAndrews, Frances, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978184615497340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846154973423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846154973/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles